	An Instance of Treason: Ozaki Hotsumi and the Sorge Spy Ring

	By Chalmers A. Johnson

	The Manchurian Incident, as this action was called, was the opening scene in the Sino-Japanese war of 1937-45. It took the civilian Japanese government in Tokyo by surprise, and made it clear for the first time that the Japanese Army had passed beyond formal governmental control and intended to become a prime formulator, rather than an instrument, of Japanese foreign and domestic policy. It surprised Sorge and Ozaki, too.


