	...After the February Revolution of 1905 in Russia, several refugees and revolutionaries had made their way to Nagasaki. There they formed a revolutionary party with Dr. Nicolai Russel at its head. ...In 1906 Sun Yat-sen traveled to Annam with Kayano Chochi. On his way, he met Russel. The two discussed general problems, and agreed that their revolutions had complementary aims. 
	
	...Miyazaki, Kayano, and several others met these Russians in 1906. Together with several socialists, they published a magazine called Kakumei hyoron (Revolutionary review) which was to speed both revolutions.


